content:
Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "In an aquarium, we may want to have different fish objects instantiated from each of the `AreaFish`, `Fish2D`, and `Fish` classes. If we wanted to add a new method named `die` to make the fish disappear, to which class or classes should we add this new method?",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "Any one of these three classes. After defining the die() method in either of them, we will be able to call it from other classes as well.",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "Only the `Fish` class, as it will be reflected in the other classes.",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "Only the `AreaFish` class, as this class is like a superset containing all properties and behaviors.",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "It should be added to all the three classes.",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Do the question text and it's choices provide enough information or context for a student to answer it correctly?
